{"title": "Spiking the Camera", "content": "A specific form of Breaking the Fourth Wall accomplished merely by looking directly at the camera. Usually done by accident, by amateur actors who happen to notice a camera is pointed at them. The trouble here is that the editor didn't catch it, allowing the character to make eye contact with the audience. Typically a film or live TV trope, especially in dramas.\n\nIntentional occurrences fall under Aside Glance or Fourth-Wall Observer.\n\nContrast with No Fourth Wall (thus including documentaries and reality TV), where the cast is aware of the audience, which \u0097 in turn \u0097 is aware of the production crew. Not to be confused with actually spiking a camera, which would probably fall under Camera Abuse.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpikingTheCamera", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ANightAtTheOpera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SurfsUp", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CaptainAmericaTheFirstAvenger", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DazedAndConfused", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HotFuzz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TimothyDalton", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/EdgarWright", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LoveActually", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KeiraKnightley", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ANightAtTheOpera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PansLabyrinth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheRockyHorrorPictureShow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ANewHope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheTenCommandments", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TomBaker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/WilliamHartnell", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/GreenAcres", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FinalFantasyV", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/Twitter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TomBaker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HouseOfCardsUK"]